    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-10-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="447"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d447">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">the Marquis
                        de Montholon</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-10-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 31, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 19th instant in regard to violation of neutrality of the United
                    States alleged to have taken place recently on the Rio Grande. In reply, I have
                    the honor to inform you that I have requested the Secretary of War to cause the
                    matter to be inquired into with a view to the adoption of such proceedings as
                    may be called for.</p>
                <p>Accept, sir, a renewed assurance of my highest consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>The <hi rend="smallcaps">Marquis de Montholon</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
